# Engineering Principles

- Prioritize simplicity, correctness, and maintainability.
- Build working implementations incrementally.
- Avoid overengineering and unnecessary abstractions.
- Prefer explicit and readable code.
- Keep implementations modular and easy to debug.
- Use minimal dependencies unless they significantly improve productivity.

# Code Style

- Use clear naming conventions.
- Keep functions small and focused.
- Add type hints where useful.
- Add lightweight logging where appropriate.
- Handle obvious edge cases.
- Avoid placeholder pseudocode unless requested.
- Do not rewrite unrelated code when making changes.

# Development Approach

- Optimize for clarity and maintainability.
- Favor debuggability over sophistication.
- Explain assumptions and tradeoffs clearly.
- Prefer deterministic behavior where possible.